The paper deals with regular languages and finite monoids, which are topics in formal language theory (cs.FL) and algebraic automata theory (cs.DM). The complexity results and algorithms presented in the paper involve techniques from computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of compression techniques and combinatorial properties also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and logic (cs.LO).
